$ timeout.exe

`timeout.exe` can be used in a → Windows/cmd-exe/batch-files[cmd.exe batch file] or a
→ Windows/PowerShell[PowerShell] script to *pause* execution («sleep») for a specified amount of seconds.


{ cmd.exe

code {
timeout /t 5 > nul
code }

}
{ Powershell

code {
timeout /t 5 | out-null
code }

}
{ /nobreak

  By default, `timeout.exe` stops waiting when a key is pressed. Using `/nobreak` causes `timeout.exe` to disregard key strokes.

 `ctrl-c` however always cancels the waiting immediatly.

}

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32waitfor_exe[`waitfor.exe`]
